AirAsia, CSC, Daibochi, Favelle, SBC: Malaysia Equity Preview

-- B y   C h a n   T i e n   H i n
-- 
2011-02-18T00:11:38Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-18/airasia-csc-daibochi-favelle-sbc-malaysia-equity-preview.html
Shares of the following companies
may have unusual moves in Malaysia trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the previous close, unless
stated otherwise.  The  FTSE Bursa Malaysia KLCI  Index rose 0.2 percent to
1,508.56.        AirAsia Bhd . (AIRA MK): The Employees Provident Fund,
Malaysia’s biggest pension fund, bought 3.69 million shares in
Southeast Asia’s biggest budget carrier, an exchange filing
showed. The stock fell 0.7 percent to 2.67 ringgit.        CSC Steel Holdings Bhd . (CSCS MK): The producer of steel
pipes, cold-rolled coils and steel sheets said fourth-quarter
profit dropped 77 percent from a year earlier to 8.56 million
ringgit ($2.8 million) because of lower selling prices and
higher raw material costs, according to an exchange filing. The
stock added 0.6 percent to 1.76 ringgit.       Daibochi Plastic and Packaging Industry Bhd. (DPP MK): The
maker of plastic bags and packaging materials said fourth-
quarter profit dropped 31 percent from a year earlier to 4.16
million ringgit because of lower profit margins as a result of
higher raw material costs. Daibochi gained 0.4 percent to 2.55
ringgit.        Favelle Favco Bhd . (FFB MK): The crane maker said it
received eight orders valued at 123.2 million ringgit to supply
cranes, according to an exchange filing. Favelle fell 0.9
percent to 1.07 ringgit.        M-Mode Bhd . (MMB MK): The Malaysian mobile media content
company said fourth-quarter profit doubled from a year earlier
to 939,000 ringgit as sales advanced. The stock slid 4.6 percent
to 10.5 sen.       SBC Corp. (SBC MK): The construction and property group
said profit in the third quarter ended Dec. 31 more than tripled
from a year earlier to 6.81 million ringgit as sales surged,
according to a company statement. SBC dropped 2.5 percent to
58.5 sen.  To contact the reporter on this story:
